==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syrphus fly
<hw>Syr"phus fly`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[NL. <ets>Syrphus</ets>, the
generic name, fr. Gr. <?/, <?/, a kind of winged insect.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of dipterous flies
of the genus <gen>Syrphus</gen> and allied genera. They are usually
bright-colored, with yellow bands, and hover around plants. The larvae
feed upon plant lice, and are, therefore, very beneficial to
agriculture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syrt</ent>⟦br⟧
